question: 兄貴
sourceMnemonic: The <kanji>older brother</kanji> is <kanji>valuable</kanji> to you. But, no matter how valuable he is to you, he's still just your <vocabulary>older brother</vocabulary>. P.S. You'll often see some gangstah thug call a higher ranking gangstah thug (one that acts like an older brother to all the other gangstah thugs) this. It's like family within the gang.
sourceReadingMnemonic: The reading is <ja>兄</ja> on its own plus the reading for <ja>貴</ja>. ANIKIIIII.
